<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100797352125176></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100797352125176><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=7032&mid=100797352125176>RE: Damage Bonus...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=7032&mid=100797352125176#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=71807><span id= >Coravix</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 3:38 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>there's a difference between a dmg bonus and a dmg cap. a dmg cap means that you do less than the maximum potential (ie and only an example: out of 100 possible pnts dmg, if yer cap is 50, ye can do a max of 50) and that cap is raised at certain levels. (20 and 30 i beleive) this means at those lvls you can do more dmg, but still only up to the max dmg (100 in the example). it just looks like yer doing bonus dmg but yer not, yer just not being as gimped as ye were before (say doing 75 pnts max instead of 50 max.. looks higher, but it's still less than the max)<br><br>on the other hand a dmg bonus means that you get this dmg over and above the max dmg (side note: i don't beleive this raises minimum dmg cause i still get sucky 1dmg hits with a +7 dmg bonus). in the above example if you have a dmg Bonus of 10 ye'd do 110 dmg.<br><br><br>the reason this makes such an impac at higher lvls is cause with a low enough delay and fast enough weapon, yer dmg bonus tiems the number of yer hits ends up being more dmg than a slower weapon's high seeming dmg.  got to borrow another war's lammi (he wanted to try my WS) and i noticed a hell of a difference. yeah, i would get nice 90+ pnt hits with WS **once in a while** but my avg hits were only slightly less with the lammi (35-45 avg with WS, 25-35 with lammi) but were striking twice as fast (ex: 10 hits at 45 would be 450 dmg, 20 hits at 30 is 600).<br><br><br>*hopes that made sense, i've a Hate raid hangover*<br><br><br>-me<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
